HEADWORD: Hendiadys
<hw>Hen*di"a*dys</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <?/
<?/ <?/ one by two.]</ety> <fld>(Gram.)</fld> <def>A figure in which the
idea is expressed by two nouns connected by <xex>and</xex>, instead of
by a noun and limiting adjective; <as>as, we drink from <ex>cups and
gold</ex>, for <ex>golden cups</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
